 24, 2020}}</ref>\n| OriginalISBN    = 9784049127980\n| LicensedRelDate = \u2014\n| LicensedISBN    = \n| ChapterList     =\n| LicensedTitle   = Mist\n| OriginalTitle   = \u30df\u30b9\u30c8\n| TranslitTitle   = Misuto\n| Summary         = \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n| VolumeNumber    = 8\n| OriginalRelDate = May 9, 2020<ref name=\"jp-novel-8\">{{cite web|url=https://dengekibunko.jp/product/86/322002000076.html|title=\uff18\uff16\u2015\u30a8\u30a4\u30c6\u30a3\u30b7\u30c3\u30af\u30b9\u2015Ep.8 \u2015\u30ac\u30f3\u30b9\u30e2\u30fc\u30af\u30fb\u30aa\u30f3\u30fb\u30b6\u30fb\u30a6\u30a9\u30fc\u30bf\u30fc\u2015|language=Japanese|publisher=[[ASCII Media Works]]|accessdate=April 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| OriginalISBN    = 9784049131857\n| LicensedRelDate = \u2014\n| LicensedISBN    = \n| ChapterList     =\n| LicensedTitle   = Gun Smoke On the Water\n| OriginalTitle   = \u30ac\u30f3\u30b9\u30e2\u30fc\u30af\u30fb\u30aa\u30f3\u30fb\u30b6\u30fb\u30a6\u30a9\u30fc\u30bf\u30fc\n| TranslitTitle   = Gan\tSumoku On Za Uota\t\n| Summary         = \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list/footer}}\n\n===Manga===\nA [[manga]] adaptation by Motoki Yoshihara has been serialized in [[Square Enix]]'s [[seinen manga|''seinen'' manga]] magazine ''[[Young Gangan]]'' since 2018. It has been collected in two ''[[tank\u014dbon]]'' volumes. A second manga adaptation titled ''Gakuen 86'' by Suzume Somemiya has been announced. It will be serialized in [[Media Factory]]'s ''seinen'' manga magazine ''[[Monthly Comic Alive]]''.<ref name=\"ANN1\"/>\n\n{{Graphic novel list/header\n| Language     = Japanese\n| OneLanguage  = yes\n| Width        = 75%\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n| VolumeNumber = 1\n| RelDate      = October 10, 2018<ref name=\"jp-manga-1\">{{cite web|url=https://magazine.jp.square-enix.com/top/comics/detail/9784757558700/|title=86\u30fc\u30a8\u30a4\u30c6\u30a3\u30b7\u30c3\u30af\u30b9\u30fc 1|language=Japanese|publisher=[[Young Gangan]]|accessdate=March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n| ISBN         = 9784757558700\n| ChapterList  =\n| Summary      = \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n| VolumeNumber = 2\n| RelDate      = September 10, 2019<ref name=\"jp-manga-2\">{{cite web|url=https://magazine.jp.square-enix.com/top/comics/detail/9784757562783/|title=86\u30fc\u30a8\u30a4\u30c6\u30a3\u30b7\u30c3\u30af\u30b9\u30fc 2|language=Japanese|publisher=[[Young Gangan]]|accessdate=March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n| ISBN         = 9784757562783\n| ChapterList  =\n| Summary      = \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list/footer}}\n\n===Anime===\nAn [[anime]] television series adaptation was announced in a livestream commemorating the first anniversary of [[Kadokawa Corporation|Kadokawa]]'s \"Kimirano\" light novel website on March 15, 2020.<ref name=\"ANN1\"/> It is produced by [[A-1 Pictures]] and directed by Toshimasa Ishii, with Toshiya Ono writing the scripts, and Tetsuya Kawakami designing the characters. The series is scheduled to air in 2020.<ref name=\"ANN2\">{{cite web|first=Crystalyn|last=Hodgkins|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-03-22/86-sci-fi-battle-anime-reveals-cast-staff-2020-premiere/.157809|title='86' Sci-Fi Battle Anime Reveals Cast, Staff, 2020 Premiere|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=March 22, 2020|accessdate=March 22, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nThe light novel won the Grand Prize at the 24th [[Dengeki Novel Prize]] award in 2016.<ref name=\"ANN2\"/> The light novel also ranked second in 2018 in [[Takarajimasha]]'s annual light novel guide book ''[[Kono Light Novel ga Sugoi!]]'', in the ''[[bunkobon]]'' category.<ref>{{cite web|first=Rafael Antonio|last=Pineda|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-11-24/kono-light-novel-ga-sugoi-reveals-2018-series-ranking/.124444|title=Kono Light Novel ga Sugoi! Reveals 2018 Series Ranking|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=November 24, 2017|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref> It ranked fifth in 2019.<ref>{{cite web|first=Rafael Antonio|last=Pineda|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-11-23/kono-light-novel-ga-sugoi-reveals-2019-series-ranking/.139859|title=Kono Light Novel ga Sugoi! Reveals 2019 Series Ranking|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=November 23, 2018|accessdate=March 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|https://dengekibunko.jp/product/86/|Official light novel website}} {{in lang|ja}}\n*{{Official website|https://magazine.jp.square-enix.com/yg/introduction/86/|Official manga website}} {{in lang|ja}}\n*{{Official website|https://anime-86.com/|Official anime website}} {{in lang|ja}}\n*{{ann|light novel|21185}}\n*{{ann|anime|23089}}\n\n{{Gangan Comics manga franchises}}\n{{A-1 Pictures}}\n\n[[Category:2017 Japanese novels]]\n[[Category:A-1 Pictures]]\n[[Category:Anime and manga based on light novels]]\n[[Category:Dengeki Bunko]]\n[[Category:Gangan Comics manga]]\n[[Category:Japanese science fiction novels]]\n[[Category:Light novels]]\n[[Category:Media Factory manga]]\n[[Category:Science fiction anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Seinen manga]]\n[[Category:Square Enix manga]]\n[[Category:Upcoming anime television series]]\n[[Category:Yen Press titles]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Japanese light novel series}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| name            = 86\n| image           = 86 light novel volume 1 cover.jpg\n| caption         = Cover of the first light novel volume published by ''[[ASCII Media Works]]'', featuring Shinei N\u014dzen (left) and Vladilena Miriz\u00e9 (right)\n| ja_kanji        = 86-\u30a8\u30a4\u30c6\u30a3\u30b7\u30c3\u30af\u30b9-\n| ja_romaji       = Eiti Shikkusu\n| genre           = [[Science fiction]]<ref name=\"ANN1\"/>\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = light novel\n| author          = Asato Asato\n| illustrator     = Shirabi\n| publisher       = [[ASCII Media Works]]\n| publisher_en    = {{English manga publisher|NA=[[Yen Press]]}}\n| demographic     = Male\n| imprint         = [[Dengeki Bunko]]\n| first           = February 10, 2017\n| last            = \n| volumes         = 7\n| volume_list     